Fixed logic in TimeZoneRule::isDSTActive().  This fixes the bug I reported
on kstars-devel yesterday, regarding bad DST settings for Chilean
locations (this probably also fixes informal reports we've had about DST
problems in Australia, as any Southern Hemisphere location which observes
DST was likely affected).  Will backport to 3_1_BRANCH; too bad I missed
3.1.3  :(

The bug itself was kind of interesting.  The original code was:
  if ( StartMonth < RevertMonth )
    if ( month < StartMonth || month > RevertMonth ) return false;
  else
    if ( month < StartMonth && month > RevertMonth ) return false;


which I replaced with:
  if ( StartMonth < RevertMonth ) {
    if ( month < StartMonth || month > RevertMonth ) return false;
  } else {
    if ( month < StartMonth && month > RevertMonth ) return false;
  }

Think those are functionally identical?  Think again! ;)

